              "id": "CVE-2026-22732",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Spring Security: Spring Security: Security policy bypass and information disclosure due to unwritten HTTP headers"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "When applications specify HTTP response headers for servlet applications using Spring Security, there is the possibility that the HTTP Headers will not be written. \nThis issue affects Spring Security Servlet applications using lazy (default) writing of HTTP Headers:\n\n: from 5.7.0 through 5.7.21, from 5.8.0 through 5.8.23, from 6.3.0 through 6.3.14, from 6.4.0 through 6.4.14, from 6.5.0 through 6.5.8, from 7.0.0 through 7.0.3."
